{"id":14881046,"mediaExerciseId":"a322f2d2-d5bc-438c-8d5e-a37cde8cf5fb","exerciseName":"12","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612312,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":233,"solutions":[{"id":6395736,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are tasked with analyzing the approximate and exact real rate of interest on a treasury bond.\n\nLet's get started!","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"We'll start by explaining what the real rate of return of a bond is and how it's calculated.\n\nThe annual percentage of income generated on an investment, adjusted for inflation, is the real rate of return. As a result, the real rate of return accurately describes the purchasing power of a given quantity of money over time.\n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The approximate real rate of interest is calculated by subtracting the inflation rate from the nominal rate of return:\n\n$$\\text{AROI} = \\text{Nominal rate of return} - \\text{Inflation rate}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":" The Fisher equation, which shows the exact relationship between nominal interest rates, real interest\nrates, and inflation is:\n$$(1 + R) = (1 + r)(1 + h) $$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"We are given the following information on the treasury bill:\n\n1. The nominal rate of return is 5.1%\n2. The inflation rate is 2.2%","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"By inputting the given values into Eq.$(1)$, we get the following approximate rate of return:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{AROI} &= 5.1\\% - 2.2\\% \\\\[10pt]\n&= 2.9\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"8efdd4ae-a1ff-4d70-a44a-8dfefd447381","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881047,"exerciseName":"13","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"5044fdd6-4e5a-4ea1-8a4e-365c36092f45","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-13-5044fdd6-4e5a-4ea1-8a4e-365c36092f45"},{"id":14881048,"exerciseName":"14","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a8a0a30f-3f41-4ff6-9c4e-bb4649e034a0","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-14-a8a0a30f-3f41-4ff6-9c4e-bb4649e034a0"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881045,"exerciseName":"11","page":232,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"cfe24fe5-37b8-4e02-a060-a4f31655013e","_webUrl":"https://qu